The Educators Union of South Africa is taking government to court. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Educators Union of South Africa (Eusa) is taking the government to court. Eusa wants to stop schools reopening for Grade 7 and 12 pupils next week. READ: Key points from Angie Motshekga's plan The union represents over 27,000 teachers. Eusa says Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga and her department misled the public about supplying personal protective equipment and guaranteeing the safety of pupils and teachers.